{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the performance of LLMs in information extraction, text summarization, and QA cannot be directly equated to their effectiveness in key-insight extraction tasks.",
    "Therefore, it is necessary to systematically evaluate the performance of LLMs on key-insight extraction tasks.",
    "The key behind achieving high performance of LLMs lies in the two main stages of the training process: (1) initial pre-training on massive text corpora, endowing the LLM with an expansive grasp of linguistic knowledge and structure; (2) fine-tuning on specific tasks to adapt to distinct domains and applications.",
    "This dual-training paradigm equips LLMs with unparalleled adaptability, rendering them instrumental in the modern landscape of natural language processing.",
    "Since initial pre-training of LLMs requires a large amount of hardware support, scholars tend to fine-tune the pre-trained LLMs to adapt to tasks in different fields 24."
  ]
}